{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You want me to answer your questions?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. HILL
{META_DATA}: (sarcastic)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry if I was being vague -- yes, I do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Who's going to answer mine, you dick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Hill stares at her before closing up his files.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (raising voice)
{DIALOGUE}: What happened to my child today?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Hill gets up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Something was happening to him -- physically happening.
{DIALOGUE}: Something was very wrong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Hill hands his files to MRS. SLOAN and exits the reception room without looking back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everyone in the reception room stares at Lynn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Sloan walks up to the table and waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn takes a second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wipes her eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gathers her considerable strength.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: How long will these questions take?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOSPITAL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole lays rigid in the hospital bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blankets bundled around him as if to shield him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's eyes fixed out the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm quietly enters through the half-opened door to the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole spots him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Visibly relaxes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I've decided we shouldn't schedule sessions anymore.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll just follow you around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole smiles weakly as Malcolm takes a seat on a rolling metal chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm notices Cole's legs emerging from under the hospital gown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is wearing A MAN'S DRESS SOCK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The baggy folds ride up all the way to his knees.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Your father ever tell you bedtime stories?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks at Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm makes a decision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls in the chair across the room as he thinks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Once upon a time there was a prince, who was being driven around... He drove around for a long, long time... Driving and driving... It was a long trip... He fell asleep...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: When he woke up, they were still driving... The long drive went on--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Crowe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You haven't told bedtime stories before?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You have to add some twists and stuff.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe they run out of gas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: No gas... Hey, that's good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They sit in silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm works on a new plot in his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me a story about why you're sad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think I'm sad?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole nods, "Yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What makes you think that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Your eyes told me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's affected by his client.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (rote)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not supposed to talk about stuff like that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole smiles softly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stares at the tired child sitting before him in the hospital bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm rolls his stool away from his client as he thinks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly moves the rolling chair closer to Cole's bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: ...Once upon a time there was this person named Malcolm.
{DIALOGUE}: He worked with children.
{DIALOGUE}: Loved it more than anything.
{META_DATA}: (smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: Then one night, he finds out he made a mistake with one of them.
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't help that one at all.
{DIALOGUE}: He thinks about that one a lot.
{DIALOGUE}: Can't forget.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Ever since then, things have been different.
{DIALOGUE}: He's become messed up.
{DIALOGUE}: Confused.
{DIALOGUE}: Angry.
{DIALOGUE}: Not the same person he used to be.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: His wife doesn't like the person he's become.
{DIALOGUE}: They don't speak anymore.
{DIALOGUE}: They're like strangers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm breaks from his thoughts and looks at Cole who watches him with unwavering attention.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: And then one day this person Malcolm meets a wonderful boy who reminds him of that one.
{DIALOGUE}: Reminds him a lot of that one.
{DIALOGUE}: Malcolm decides to try to help this new boy.
{DIALOGUE}: He thinks maybe if he can help this boy, it would be like helping that one too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans forward, whispers with emotional eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know how the story ends.
{DIALOGUE}: I hope it's a happy ending.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Me too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks at Malcolm's caring eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at Malcolm a long time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: EVERYTHING THAT'S SAID FROM THIS POINT ON IS WHISPERED.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I want to tell you my secret now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm blinks very slowly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole takes an eternal pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A silent tension engulfs them both.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: ...I see people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm just gazes quietly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I see dead people... Some of them scare me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: In your dreams?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole shakes his head, "No."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: When you're awake?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole nods, "Yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Dead people, like in graves and coffins?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: No, walking around, like regular people... They can't see each other.
{DIALOGUE}: Some of them don't know they're dead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: They don't know they're dead?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I see ghosts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm becomes completely motionless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Works to hide his shock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and Cole stare at each other a long time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: They tell me stories... Things that happened to them... Things that happened to people they know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's words are extra-controlled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Revealing nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: How often do you see them?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: All the time.
{DIALOGUE}: They're everywhere.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You won't tell anyone my secret, right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: ...No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Will you stay here till I fall asleep?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods, "Yes."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole pulls the covers up to his chin and turns to the window in the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm is very still and stares at Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MALCOLM'S EYES -- slowly turn and survey the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They find nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm returns to watching Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE'S EYES LOOK AROUND THE ROOM WARILY... WE MOVE IN ON THEM -- TILL HIS EYES FILL THE FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then we see what he's staring at.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through Cole's hospital room window we see the adjacent wing of the hospital building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rows of hospital room windows are visible.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the windows are patients... SOME OLD, SOME YOUNG... SOME ARE DRESSED IN MODERN HOSPITAL GOWNS... SOME FROM DECADES PAST.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEY STAND UNNATURALLY STILL IN THEIR WINDOWS... WATCHING, WAITING.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET CORNER - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm hails a cab.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps off the sidewalk lost in his thoughts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Steam rises from a street vent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HEADLIGHTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CAR SUDDENLY EMERGES FROM THE STEAM, NARROWLY MISSING MALCOLM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm jerks out of the way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His briefcase falls to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His tape recorder falls to the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm reaches down and picks it up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Cole...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: His pathology is more severe than initially assessed.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: He's suffering from visual hallucinations, paranoia -- Symptoms of some kind of school age Schizophrenia.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Medication and hospitalization may be required.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's hand with the tape recorder drops to his side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not helping him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stares into the night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands alone as thoughts crash like thunder in his head.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The STREETS TURN RED as Lynn drives home from the hospital in silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances down to her right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is curled up asleep on the passenger seat, back in his regular clothes, a tiny party hat clutched in his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks like a four-year-old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sight of him exhausted and still, hits Lynn hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's face drowns in deep concern.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She lays a hand on Cole's head as she drives.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COLE'S HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front door opens, Lynn carries Cole in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's asleep on her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She carries him down the hall to his BEDROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn lays Cole gently on his bed next to his German Shepherd Puppy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole curls up with Sebastian.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn watches the two youngsters sleep for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is curled up asleep with a tiny party hat clutched in his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks like a four-year-old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn has been carrying Cole's sweater from over her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pulls it off and begins to fold it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her attention is drawn to the sweater.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She fingers the fabric of the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT'S RIPPED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes move to Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the middle of the back of his T-shirt are THREE SMALL TEARS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn pushes the fabric open with her fingers and sees DEEP FINGERNAIL LIKE SCRATCHES on his skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks around helplessly, fear creeping into her eyes.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn emerges from Cole's room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns OFF THE HALL LIGHTS as she moves into her room and closes the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR LYNN PICK UP A PHONE AND DIAL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, this is Lynn Sear, Cole's mother.
{DIALOGUE}: I wonder if we could talk about your son and his friends keeping their goddamn hands off my boy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The thermostat on the wall reads seventy-eight degrees.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few hours later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house seems threateningly still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Too still.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COLE'S HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An unnatural silence fills each room of the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The thermostat on the wall now reads, fifty-two degrees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LIGHT TURNS ON FROM UNDER COLE'S DOOR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens a crack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's tiny face peeks out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eyes scan the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens a little bit more.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's knees are pressed together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His body dances a little.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole has to pee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves cautiously into the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole moves briskly to a door halfway down the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Opens it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole turns on the LIGHT IN THE BATHROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks behind the shower curtain, before he turns his back and pees into the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LARGE FIGURE MOVES PAST THE DOORWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole instantly stops peeing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His body becomes very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly reaches for the toilet handle and flushes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He closes his pants and turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't come out of the bathroom at first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He just stands there and stares into the darkness of the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS BREATH FORMS TINY CLOUDS IN THE COLD AIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole finally steps out into the hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes catch a SLANT OF LIGHT now coming from the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole hesitates before being drawn to the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves down the hall and turns the corner -- coming to a stop in the doorway of the kitchen.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at the back of a person cooking food on the stove.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's fear slowly fades away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Momma?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Dream about daddy again?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The person turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's not Lynn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a strange woman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman's face is demented.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A purple gash cuts across her forehead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ALL THE CABINETS AND DRAWERS ARE OPEN BEHIND HER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: DINNER'S -- NOT -- READY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's face turns the color of ash.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: What are you going to do?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole backs up to the doorway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: You can't hurt me anymore!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman smiles menacingly as she thrusts her wrists forward... They've been savagely cut.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole turns and runs down the hall.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole runs across his room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He heads right for the homemade tent seated in the corner with the "DO NOT TOUCH" sign on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He scurries in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His legs disappear as the bedsheets flap closed behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crazed woman stands at the end of the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doesn't come any closer.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TENT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is curled up in the tent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lays still for a moment reaching over and FLICKING ON A FLASHLIGHT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The red interior of the tent gets LIP UP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a striking sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bedsheet walls of the tent are lined with religious pictures taped to the walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tiny statues of saints surround the interior perimeter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the statue Cole stole from the church is in here... This tent is a sanctuary made by an eight-year-old to hide in.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. AUDITORIUM STAGE - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE LIGHTS IN THE GYM GO DOWN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE SPOT LIGHT OPENS ON THE STAGE AS THE CURTAINS MOVE TO THE SIDES...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sign to the side of the stage reads, "The third and fourth grade presents -- Rudyard Kipling's "The Jungle Book."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The parents APPLAUD AS TOMMY TAMMISIMO WALKS OUT ON STAGE in a villager's outfit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOMMY
{META_DATA}: (Decent British accent)
{DIALOGUE}: There once was a boy, very different than other boys.
{DIALOGUE}: He lived in the jungle, and he could talk with the animals.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACKSTAGE, Mr. Cunningham cues the rest of the children.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE AUDIENCE APPLAUDS AS THE FULL CAST OF THE ACTORS COME OUT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some are villagers, others are dressed as trees and animals.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole comes on stage holding a painted cardboard monkey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MALCOLM APPLAUDS FROM THE BACK OF THE AUDITORIUM.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SCHOOL CORRIDOR - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The arched halls of the private school are lined with posted drawings and test papers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and Malcolm walk down an empty hall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Did you think the play sucked big time?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Tommy Tammisimo acted in a cough syrup commercial.
{DIALOGUE}: He thought everybody was self-conscious and unrealistic.
{DIALOGUE}: He said the play sucked big time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I know every child is special in their own way, but Tommy sounds like a punk.
{META_DATA}: (Cole smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: I thought the play was excellent.
{DIALOGUE}: Better than Cats.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Cats?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Never mind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They continue down the hall in silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm takes his time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, I was really interested in what you told me in the hospital, I'd like to hear more about it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stops at a set of doors at the end of the hall -- realizes Cole is no longer next to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns to find Cole frozen about ten feet back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm walks to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He notices Cole's expression as he gets closer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What's wrong?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole points to the doors.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Is something in there?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole doesn't say anything.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GYMNASIUM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a large shadowy GYM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Climbing ropes hang from the wood beamed ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is trembling slightly as he stands next to Malcolm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What is it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm follows the child's gaze to the ceiling of the gym.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't see.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Be real still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks to Cole and then turns back to the ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's body becomes very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes you feel it inside.
{DIALOGUE}: Like you're falling down real fast, but you're really just standing still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks at the wood beams and climbing ropes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You ever feel prickly things on the back of your neck?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: And the tiny hairs on your arm.
{DIALOGUE}: Are they all standing up?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm glances at Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Surprise on his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: -- Yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: When they get mad, it gets cold.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Them?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks at the empty stairwell and then back to Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing is said for a few moments.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't see anything.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure they're there?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Cole?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns back to Cole, he finds the child with tears in his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks at Malcolm desperately.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Please make them leave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stares helplessly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm working on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm gently leads Cole away from the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE GLANCES BACK AS HE MOVES OUT OF THE STAIRWELL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE'S P.O.V. -- The ropes and school banners dangling at the top of the stairs sways a little... But so do THE THREE BODIES HANGING BY THEIR NECKS FROM A WOODEN BEAM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a truly horrific sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BLACK MAN in britches and no shirt, face beaten to a pulp, hangs in the center.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A WHITE WOMAN in a torn white frilly dress -- tears soaking her face, hangs to the right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small MIXED RACE CHILD in half pants, hangs to their left.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The family stares at Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They follow Cole with their tortured eyes as he exits the stairwell.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HISTORIC PHILADELPHIA - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm walks from the bus stop over the cobblestone streets in front of Head House Square.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The streets are quiet and dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Night time has fallen over the city.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly comes to a stop in front of an old building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds his arm up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uses his other hand to gently touch his hairs on his arm's surface.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks up slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dark shadows fill the corners of the historic building...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stares into the darkness... Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: ...Is anyone there?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long moment as he waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shadows seem to move, then becomes still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm shakes off the moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He returns his hands to his pockets as he moves through the dark streets of Philadelphia to his home.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doorway to Malcolm and Anna's bedroom is open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STRAINED VOICES SPILL OUT INTO THE HALLWAY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM (o.s.)
{DIALOGUE}: Look, he's an eight-year-old child.
{DIALOGUE}: He's my only client.
{DIALOGUE}: If he invites me to his play, I'm not thinking about how late I get back... I go.
{DIALOGUE}: I have to go.
{DIALOGUE}: You know that.
{DIALOGUE}: That's the only way I know how to work.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Vincent said I failed him.
{META_DATA}: (raising his voice)
{DIALOGUE}: I WON'T GIVE COLE A CHANCE TO SAY THOSE WORDS TO ME!
{DIALOGUE}: I WON'T!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE PORTABLE PHONE RINGS OUT IN THE HALL.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM (o.s.)
{DIALOGUE}: Please let it ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR MOVEMENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna emerges from the bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eyes raw.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wipes her tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She picks up the phone and moves down the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm walks out into the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stops at the top of the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANNA'S VOICE CAN BE HEARD SPEAKING ON THE PHONE from downstairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: I can't talk now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm doesn't hear anything as Anna listens to the person on the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles as she wipes her tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts for the basement door again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: I thought about you too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands frozen at the top of the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna's HUSHED WORDS RISING IN THE AIR LIKE A GUN BLAST.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn adjusts the thermostat as she tries to keep herself warm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't care what they say, this thing is definitely broken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn fiddles with the dials.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is standing before the beat-up twelve inch kitchen T.V.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE TELEVISION SCREEN is Tommy Tammisimo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands in his pajamas in a doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He coughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOMMY
{META_DATA}: (on T.V.)
{DIALOGUE}: Mommy, my throat hurts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole watches as Tommy's T.V. mother and father give him a spoonful of medicine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NARRATOR
{META_DATA}: (on T.V.)
{DIALOGUE}: Pediaease Cough Suppressant... gentle, fast, effective.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole watches Tommy running around in his T.V. background, the very next T.V. morning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's not sick anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tommy waves to the camera smiling and healthy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T.V. goes BLACK as Cole throws his shoe at the power button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves to the dinner table where Lynn is seated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole sits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hands go on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's wearing a pair of his father's extra large LEATHER GLOVES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's small hands don't even fill the palm area.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole has difficulty trying to pick up his milk glass with the gloves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Take 'em off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole removes the gloves from his hand and places them next to his plate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want them on my table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole moves them to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn is irritated, this is a sore point between them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn and Cole eat quietly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I saw what was in your bureau drawer when I was cleaning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An anxious expression on his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You got something you want to confess?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole just stares.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: The bumble bee pendant.
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you keep taking it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks down at his lap.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It was Grandma's.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not for playing.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: What if it broke?
{DIALOGUE}: You know how sad I'd be.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You'd cry.
{DIALOGUE}: Cause you miss grandma so much.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{DIALOGUE}: So why do you take it, sweetheart?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes people think they lose things and they didn't really lose them.
{DIALOGUE}: It just gets moved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Did you move the bumble bee pendant?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole shakes his head, "No."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn just stares.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't take it before.
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't take it the time after that.
{DIALOGUE}: And now, you didn't take it again?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't get mad.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: So who moved it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole doesn't answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: There's only two of us.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe someone came in our house -- took the bumble bee pendant out of my closet, and then laid it nicely in your drawer?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Is that what happened?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn just stares at Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm so tired, Cole.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tired in my body.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tired in my mind.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tired in my heart.
{DIALOGUE}: I need a little help here.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know if you noticed -- but our little family isn't doing so good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn folds her napkin quietly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm praying for us, but I must not be praying right.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: It looks like we're just going to have to answer each other's prayers.
{DIALOGUE}: If we can't talk to each other -- we're not going to make it.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Now baby, tell me... I won't be mad, honey... Did you take the bumble bee pendant?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's eyes start to water up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn goes cold.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You've had enough roast beef.
{DIALOGUE}: You need to leave the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole just stares at his mother's expression.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (yells)
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole gets up -- never taking his eyes off his mother -- and leaves the room.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole enters the DARK HALLWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets startled by the SOUND OF HIS PUPPY GROWLING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sebastian comes racing down the hall and scurries past Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole watches his puppy dart into the living room and under a couch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole slowly turns back and looks down the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DOOR TO COLE'S ROOM SITS AT THE END OF THE CORRIDOR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT'S ALMOST SHUT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE WATCHES AS THE DOOR BEGINS TO OPEN VERY SLOWLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT OPENS WIDE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE DOESN'T MOVE AN INCH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY IN THE STILLNESS AND THE DARKNESS, A SMALL FIGURE SCURRIES FROM ANOTHER BEDROOM INTO THE BLACKNESS OF COLE'S ROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT HAPPENS LIKE A FLASH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stops breathing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE FIGURE SLOWLY STEPS OUT FROM COLE'S DOORWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT'S A BOY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FEW YEARS OLDER THAN COLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE BOY WHISPERS IN A LOW, HOARSE VOICE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY
{DIALOGUE}: Come on... I'll show you where my dad keeps his gun... Come on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE BOY TURNS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE SEE THAT THE BACK OF HIS HEAD IS MISSING AS HE DISAPPEARS INTO THE DARKNESS OF COLE'S ROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is too terrified to move.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn is kneeling on the kitchen floor trying to coax the puppy out of the broom closet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE (o.s.)
{DIALOGUE}: Momma.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn turns -- surprised to hear her son's voice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's eyes are red from crying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wipes them quickly with the back of her hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mother and son look at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: If you're not very mad... Can I sleep in your room tonight?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn fights back some tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Look at my face, Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn smiles at her son.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not very mad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn hugs him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Baby... Why are you shaking?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole doesn't answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, what's wrong?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole just closes his eyes and holds his mom tight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (desperate)
{DIALOGUE}: ...Please tell me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole doesn't say a word.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (crying)
{DIALOGUE}: Please.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ANTIQUE STORE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We are in an antique store.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Filled floor to ceiling with furniture and knickknacks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna stands with a YOUNG COUPLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All three lean over and peer into a glass cabinet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An antique engagement ring sits on a velvet stand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: It's Edwardian.
{DIALOGUE}: Beautifully worked.
{DIALOGUE}: Entirely platinum with a mine cut diamond and an actual color Burmese Sapphire... It's timeless.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG MAN
{DIALOGUE}: You got anything a little plainer?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The young woman looks at her beau.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Plainer?
{DIALOGUE}: You want a plain ring to go with your plain fiance.
{DIALOGUE}: Is that how it is?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG MAN
{DIALOGUE}: No, baby.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't get in a tizzy.
{DIALOGUE}: It's just... you're so beautiful... you're like a Burmese Sapphire all by yourself.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't need all that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG WOMAN
{META_DATA}: (disbelief)
{DIALOGUE}: Uh-huh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna smiles as she takes the ring out of the cabinet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you two hold it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She places it in their hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Do you feel longing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: When I touch this piece I feel a longing.
{DIALOGUE}: I imagine the woman who owned this, loved a man deeply she couldn't be with.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The young woman looks at Anna with great intrigue.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG WOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Did he have wavy hair and broad shoulders?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The young man throws an odd glance at his fiance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know... But maybe...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: A lot of the pieces in this store give me feelings.
{DIALOGUE}: I think maybe when people own things and then they pass away -- a part of themselves gets printed on those things -- like fingerprints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The young man and the young woman gaze at Anna silently.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look down at the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They place their hands on it reverently, delicately -- like checking for a pulse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna can't hold back her sweet smile.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ANTIQUE STORE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna moves to the back desk where SEAN comes out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's carrying an antique bench in his arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He places it down and takes a much needed seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: You don't need someone with a masters.
{DIALOGUE}: You need a wrestler guy whose neck is larger than his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: I need a wrestler with a masters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna fills out the paperwork for the ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: What's this?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna looks over to find Sean standing at his desk where a BIRTHDAY PRESENT sits on his tabletop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean looks at her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: From you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna nods, "yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Is it wrestling tights?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna smiles as she moves to his desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean begins to tear off the wrapping paper like a kid at Christmas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna laughs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean holds up a weathered hardback copy of "THE GREAT GATSBY."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: It's a first edition.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Wow, this is too much.
{DIALOGUE}: It's perfect, Anna.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean puts down the book and hugs her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls back a little, still holding her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They smile at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The moment goes on just that crucial fraction of a second too long.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their smiles slowly melt away as they continue to hold each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing happens for the longest time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRASH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SHATTERING DOOR SLAM ECHOES THROUGH THE STORE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna and Jeffery pull apart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They rush past the young man and the young woman to the front of the store.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They find the glass front door cracked in a spider web pattern.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They carefully push open the door and step out onto the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Look around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one in sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna stares down the empty street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A concerned expression on her face.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm walks angrily down the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops as his hand goes to his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He winces with pain as he keeps walking.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SUPERMARKET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn and Cole emerge from the supermarket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole rides inside the shopping cart tucked between bags of food.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mother and son are quiet as they move towards their car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn leans over, looks at the side of her son's pensive face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She starts pushing the cart faster.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole wakes from his thoughts as his hair flutters in the wind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn is smiling as she pushes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole turns and raises his hands in the air like he's on a roller coaster.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They slow and come to a rest at the bumper of their car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn leans over -- sees the side of Cole's face smiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's face shows a little happiness for the first time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A little hope enters her eyes as she starts to load the groceries into the car.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and Lynn ride home with a back seat full of groceries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole finishes off a cherry popsicle as he watches out the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Let's rent a movie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole bites off the last of the popsicle and glances at his mom.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Your pick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at his mom quietly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It can even have Jean Claude Van Damme in it if you want.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole smiles at that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He nods, "Yes" joyfully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His smile fades away as he notices his mother fiddling with the HEATER controls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole gazes out the front windshield as the car moves towards home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly a piece of paper sticks to the windshield.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a page from a Playbill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A 1941 Playbill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It flies away revealing a woman in a flowing flowery dress from the 40's suddenly walks into the middle of the street as the pages of her Playbill swirl in the air.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (yells)
{DIALOGUE}: Momma, look out!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman in the flowery dress turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hand rests on her stomach.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE SEE SHE IS PREGNANT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Playbills stick to the windshield obstructing the view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn slams the brakes... Too late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE WOMAN SMASHES INTO THE FRONT GRILL OF THE CAR... HER TERROR- STRICKEN FACE COMES OVER THE HOOD AND CRASHES RIGHT THROUGH THE WINDSHIELD IN A SHOWER OF BLOOD AND GLASS...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE SCREAMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LYNN SCREAMS... THE CAR SCREECHES TO A STOP IN THE MIDDLE OF A CONGESTED INTERSECTION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The line of cars behind them suddenly hit their brakes and swerve to one side avoiding a mass collision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a few seconds, the entire intersection has come to a halt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole who has shut his eyes... slowly opens them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks around fearfully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes move to the windshield.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No broken glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And no woman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks out through the pristine windshield onto the street where cars are stopped and staring all around them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole slowly looks over to his mother.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finds her staring at him in complete and utter disbelief.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hands clutch the wheel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whites of her knuckles showing her fear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has no idea why he screamed.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DEN - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The den is very quiet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and Malcolm sit around the multi- colored table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans back in his small plastic chair -- arms folded over his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole sits slumped over the table -- eyes peering out over his arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both look like shit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You don't wanna ask me questions today?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods, "No."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Can I ask you then?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want more than anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I told you what I want.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know, Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you think about it for a while?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm doesn't respond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole watches him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I know what I want.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: My goal is to speak to my wife.
{DIALOGUE}: The way she and I used to speak.
{DIALOGUE}: Like there was no one in the world but us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: How are you going to do that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: I can't be your doctor anymore.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I haven't given my family enough attention.
{DIALOGUE}: Bad things happen when you do that.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you understand?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room falls into silence again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole speaks extra soft.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You want to go home?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stares across at Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I have to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: When?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Soon.
{DIALOGUE}: One week.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks down at his eyes full with emotion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to transfer you.
{DIALOGUE}: I know two psychologists that are exceptional--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't fail me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks up sharply.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: --What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't give up.
{DIALOGUE}: You're the only one who can help me.
{DIALOGUE}: I know it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm tries to stay composed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It doesn't work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: You want to know a secret?
{DIALOGUE}: ... I was a paper champion.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know what that means?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole shake his head, "No."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears fall down Malcolm's cheeks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't cry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I means I wasn't what everyone thought I was...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I was a fake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You weren't a paper champion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Someone else can help you.
{DIALOGUE}: Someone else can make you happy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is crying now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole wipes his eyes with his sleeve.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They sit quietly and stare at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole whispers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Crowe?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You believe me, right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long pause.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Crowe, you believe my secret, right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both just stare.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know how to answer that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole searches for the answer in Malcolm's eyes... He finds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's not the one he wanted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: How can you help me if you don't believe me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole reaches into his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulls out a PENNY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole pushes it across the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm gazes at it, then looks up at Cole's pained eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Some magic's real.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BASEMENT - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm sits stoically at his desk in his basement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes gaze at the dusty FRAMED CERTIFICATE FROM THE CITY OF PHILADELPHIA shoved between two packing boxes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans his head back against the chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stares into the shadows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Drowns in his thoughts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE CHAIR CREAKS as he slowly sits up again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes scan the room and come to a stop on a box marked with the label...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "SESSION TAPES -- VINCENT GRAY"
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BASEMENT - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tape slides into the tape player seated on Malcolm's desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm hits play.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE SOUND OF A DOOR OPENING AND CLOSING IS HEARD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry about that.
{DIALOGUE}: Hope I didn't leave you alone too long... Wow, it's cold in here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR A CHAIR MOVE AS MALCOLM SITS DOWN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then SILENCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Vincent... Why are you crying?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Vincent?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A TEN-YEAR-OLD'S VOICE ANSWERS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (on tape crying)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: What happened?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Did something upset you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VINCENT SNIFFLES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: You won't believe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: I won't believe what?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to talk anymore.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to go home, okay?
{DIALOGUE}: I want to go home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, Vincent, you can go home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE TAPE GOES TO SILENCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm just sits in the shadowy basement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't move for a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he hits the rewind button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stops it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Presses play.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: --about that.
{DIALOGUE}: Hope I didn't leave you too long... Wow, it's cold in here--
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm hits the rewind button again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lets it rewind for a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Presses play.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: --like needles either.
{DIALOGUE}: When I was a kid, I had this blood test down -- threw up chill cheese fries all over this male nurse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR VINCENT CHUCKLE SOFTLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE SOUND OF A DOOR OPENING IS HEARD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECRETARY
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me, Doctor Reed is on line two.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Vincent, I have to take this.
{DIALOGUE}: Give me a minute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VINCENT
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FOOTSTEPS AS MALCOLM AND THE SECRETARY LEAVE THE ROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DOOR CLOSES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AND THE SILENCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing happens for a long time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AND THEN WE HEAR A SUDDEN CHAIR SCREECH ACROSS THE FLOOR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VINCENT'S BREATHING QUICKENS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SLIGHT STATIC STARTS TO FILTER IN ON THE TAPE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes are locked on the spool of audio tape as it spins in the player.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's fingers move to the volume dial.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns it way up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE STATIC NOISE FROM THE TAPE FILLS THE BASEMENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans closer to the tape player.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Closes his eyes and listens... Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DEEP IN THE STATIC... ANOTHER SOUND EMERGES, WHISPERING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MAN'S VOICE IS HEARD IN THE ROOM WITH VINCENT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN'S WHISPERING
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Familia... No dejen que esto me pase... Mi familia... Yo no quiero morir... Familia...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's mouth opens in disbelief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: ...Jesus Christ.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stands on a familiar sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares into the bay window of Mr. Marschal's brownstone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside the window we see Mr. Marschal seated with a group of older gentlemen his age.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They sit around a table eating sandwiches and talking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches as Mr. Marschal tells a story to his friends.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE CAN'T HEAR WHAT HE'S SAYING, but when he finishes everyone at the table laughs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Marschal smiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm can't help smiling as well.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is not the same man he saw before.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Life has returned to this house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns and moves down the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Each step faster than the next.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CHURCH - LATE AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm moves to the front of the church down the center aisle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes scan the empty seats.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one in sight in any direction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stands in the aisle a little out of breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds his hand to his side as he winces a bit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes float up to the balcony where toy soldiers sit on the bannister.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's head pops up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Hello again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks down and studies Malcolm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You been running around?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods, "Yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: It makes you feel better?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods, "Yes" again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I like to run around.
{DIALOGUE}: It's good exercise.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You want to ask me questions now?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm shakes his head, "No."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You want to be a lance corporal in Company M, 3rd Battalion, 7th Marines?
{DIALOGUE}: We're being dispatched to the Quang Nam province.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole holds up his plastic rifleman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes show he understands now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Something happened, didn't it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, it did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you wigging out?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I am.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: We're not gonna start crying again, are we?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: No, we're not.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: What happened?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm glances around the empty church before looking back up to Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: These people... People that died and are still hanging around.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe they weren't ready to go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole studies Malcolm's passionate face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A new face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You really look better.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe they wake up that morning thinking they have a thousand things to do and a thousand days left to do them in... And then all of a sudden, it's all taken away.
{DIALOGUE}: No one asked them.
{DIALOGUE}: It's just gone...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You have nice red in your cheeks now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know what 'Yo no quiero morir' is?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole shakes his head, "No."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: It's Spanish.
{DIALOGUE}: It means... 'I don't want to die.'
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Not all the ghosts are scary, are they?
{DIALOGUE}: Like Mrs. Marschal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What do those ghosts want when they talk to you?
{DIALOGUE}: Think real careful now, Cole...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stops moving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks over the balcony railing at Malcolm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Just help.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes!
{DIALOGUE}: I think that's right!
{DIALOGUE}: ... I think they all want that.
{DIALOGUE}: Even the scary ones...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You believe now?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's stare is unwavering.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I believe both of you now.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: And I think I might know how to make them go away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You do?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods "Yes."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I think they know you're one of those guys rare people can see them.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You need to help them.
{DIALOGUE}: Each one of them.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Everyone wants to be heard.
{DIALOGUE}: Everyone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole takes a big sigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fiddles with his riflemen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: What if they don't want help?
{DIALOGUE}: What if they're just angry and they want to hurt somebody?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think that's the way it works, Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks nervous.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: How do you know for sure?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes are drawn to Cole's arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Peeking out from under his shirt sleeve are a set of cuts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm gazes at them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I don't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and Malcolm stand silently in the center aisle of the back of the church.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm moves around the corner on his street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His mind surges with thoughts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then he glances up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His steps slow to a complete stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Further down the sidewalk, coming out of the front door of his house is SEAN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's face turns to stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches as Sean comes down the front stairs and starts across the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sudden rage surges up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm moves towards Sean fast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean reaches his car and enters it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't notice the figure closing in on him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE ENGINE STARTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm reaches the car a second late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean pulls away into traffic almost hitting another car as he does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches the car disappear down the next street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns and looks up at his home with unchecked anger and overwhelming pain erupting his eyes.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm stands in his foyer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna is sitting on the stairs, phone in her hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She faces away from the front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's a ball of tension as he listens to Anna talk into the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: ...You just walked out.
{DIALOGUE}: You're probably on your way home.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm leaving this message... I just didn't get to say what I meant...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I know you're confused.
{DIALOGUE}: It's just... I'm not prepared to do this, Sean.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to be ashamed of that.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to have to make excuses for that.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: And I wanted to tell you... I bought your present wholesale from a friend.
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't even pay tax on it.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't need someone cheap like that.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: By the way, it's a non-refundable item, it's scratched on the bottom.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Are you smiling?
{DIALOGUE}: ... I hope you're smiling.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll see you at the store.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then WE HEAR ANNA GENTLY HANG UP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans back against an old radiator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes close as the SOUND OF HIS WIFE'S FOOTSTEPS RISES UP THE STAIRS.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BROWNSTONE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house is silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No movement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is in his pajamas asleep on the floor of the TENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Curled up next to him is Sebastian.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They sleep surrounded by statues and pictures.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's eyes open as he hears HIS MOTHER'S DISTANT VOICE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Cole...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, what's happening...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole quickly gets up and rushes out of the tent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His foot catches one of the chairs the tent is fastened to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stumbles out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't realize one of the bedsheets comes loose.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It folds to the ground.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't stop as he moves through the shadowy hall and pushes open his mother's bedroom door.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LYNN'S BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stands in the doorway to his mother's bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks over the room carefully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everything is still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's room is sparse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No paintings, no accessaries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bed without a frame sits in the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A table with a sewing machine fills the other side of the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS MOTHER'S VOICE turns his attention back to the bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, what's happening to you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole looks down and finds his mother laying in her bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her face contorted in deep sadness as she speaks in her sleep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Is someone hurting you?
{DIALOGUE}: ... I'll beat their asses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole smiles at his mother as he moves to her side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Touches her face with his tiny fingers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Momma, you sleep now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His touch seems to have an effect.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn becomes still in her sleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole watches her carefully.
{META_DATA}: COT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole closes the door to his mother's bedroom shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands still in the hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lets out a heavy sigh...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS BREATH ROLLS IN A TINY CLOUD IN FRONT OF HIM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's brow furrows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He breathes again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This time intentionally.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watches as his breath materializes in the suddenly ice cold air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Every muscle in Cole's eight-year-old body becomes rigid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes a second before moving through the inky darkness of the hall.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole hurries to fix his tent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He ties the collapsed bedsheet in a knot on the edge of the chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks it carefully before entering the tent.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TENT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When Cole turns around, he stops breathing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN EIGHT-YEAR-OLD GIRL VOMITS ON HERSELF IN HIS TENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She finishes and looks up at Cole with drawn eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIRL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm feeling much better now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The girl reaches out with her withered and emaciated hands -- tiny tubes hang from her wrists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She scratches Cole as he tumbles back terrified out of the tent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whole tent collapses --
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LIVING ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole runs hard out of his bedroom and down the hall to the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets down to the ground and slides under the wooden- legged couch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sebastian is already huddled in fear under the couch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole presses as far back as he can and waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE'S P.O.V. -- is of the living room floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chair legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffee table base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rugs... Everything is still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole holds his breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing happens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes his first short breaths and watches the room for any sign of movement.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COLE'S BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few minutes later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is now standing in his doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at the hunched figure covered by the collapsed tent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEAT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole makes a decision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks like he is going to cry -- fights it back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He walks towards it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reaches down and slowly pulls the sheet off the figure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The girl vomits one more time before looking up at Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIRL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm feeling much better.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and the little girl stare silently at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole holds her stare with trembling eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens his mouth -- it takes a while before the words come out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Do you want to tell me something?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PUBLIC BUS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A downtown Septa public bus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm and Cole are among the spattering of passengers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're both wearing suits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole leans his head against the glass of the scratched window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole's large eyes drink in the passing scenery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLE'S P.O.V. -- A dark, abandoned building stretches for an entire block on one side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MAN IN A GREY, FULL-BODIED UNIFORM WITH NUMBERS PRINTED ACROSS HIS CHEST... RISES OUT OF THE TALL WEEDS IN FRONT OF THE BUILDING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HE HOBBLES HIS WAY DESPERATELY TOWARDS THE BUS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS HANDS AND LEGS ARE SHACKLED... HE LUNGES OUT FOR COLE IN THE PASSING WINDOW.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SHACKLED MAN
{DIALOGUE}: My name's not Sullivan!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A GUNSHOT ECHOES IN THE AIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE MAN'S CHEST EXPLODES IN RED AS HE FALLS TO HIS KNEES SCREAMING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole jerks back from the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bus quietly drives past THE OLD PRISON BUILDING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares down at his lap and tries not to look up anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She came a long way to visit me, didn't she?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I guess she did.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole falls into deep thoughts as he stares down at his dress shoes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm slips back into silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The city bus slithers through the old Philadelphia streets working its way downtown.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOME - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A modest home sits on a corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its small lawn, groomed carefully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rows of parked cars spill out from the driveway onto the streets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People in suits and dark dresses move somberly in and out of the front door of the home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and Malcolm join the visitors as they walk slowly towards the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A frail, little girl about four years of age sits in a dark dress on the swings in front of the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Visitors say hello to her as they pass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She doesn't say anything back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Her little sister?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole nods, "Yes."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm and Cole watch her for a moment before following others into the modest corner home.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOME - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The home is packed with people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gathering of mourners is standing room only.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The AIR IS FILLED WITH DOZENS OF HUSHED CONVERSATIONS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VISITOR #1
{DIALOGUE}: ...can you imagine being a child in a bed for two years?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We move to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VISITOR #2
{DIALOGUE}: ...I think it was six.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We move to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VISITOR #3
{DIALOGUE}: ...Six separate doctors?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We move to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VISITOR #4
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: ...the little one's falling ill now...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We move to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VISITOR #5
{DIALOGUE}: ...God help them...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FAMILY PORTRAIT HANGS NEAR THE FRONT DOOR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two girls, one bigger, one smaller sit on the ground in front of their mother and father.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their smiling faces welcome the mourners.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm and Cole are standing at the bottom of a staircase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front door opens as another group arrives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm nods to Cole as the foyer fills up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two of them quietly disappear upstairs.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALLWAY - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The narrow hall is lined with boxes of medical supplies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: I.V. stands, sterile needles and pads are in the process of being taken away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boxes are piled outside a closed bedroom door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at the shut door like he doesn't want to go in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes move to the large, colorful map of the world that dons the hallway wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gazes at the many countries and continents.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I wish I were somewhere else.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: Where will you go, where no one has died?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at the map and then turns to Malcolm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't go home, okay?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I definitely won't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole turns and stares quietly at the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waits a long time before reaching for the doorknob.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GIRL'S BEDROOM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole closes the door behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and gazes at the girl's bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a hospital bed near the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The walls are covered with get-well cards and drawings from family, friends, and school children.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her shelves are filled with puppets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All shapes and sizes of puppets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to the shelf is a puppet stage and a camcorder on a mini tripod sitting next to it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole walks to the shelf and picks up a FINGER PUPPET DANCER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He places it in his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the girl's desk, is a large collection of video cassettes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The labels read, "Puppet Show Christmas 96," "Puppet Show Birthday party," "Puppet Show class trip"...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole reads the labels carefully before moving towards the closets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He passes the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN EMACIATED HAND REACHES OUT FROM BENEATH THE BED AND GRABS COLE'S ANKLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole jerks back startled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches as the girl's hand slips back under the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stays very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing happens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly bends down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hands touch the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tilts his head and looks under the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The emaciated little girl who came to his tent lays curled on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her bulging eyes glare at Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She moves suddenly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thrusts a jewelry box forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It slides across the wooden floor and stops just before Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and the sickly girl stare at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Neither of them say a word.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LIVING ROOM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room is thick with mourners.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Most are gathered around the GIRL'S MOTHER, a young woman in her late twenties.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she moves through the room to the kitchen, she receives the many cards, hugs, and flowers that are offered as condolence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Collins leaves the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches breathlessly from the doorway as Cole moves through the many adults across the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The girl's father, MR. COLLINS, a thin man in his late twenties, is seated on the reading chair next to a T.V. His face is granite.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one in the room dares to talk to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares statue-like at an abstract point in the room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Mister?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man doesn't react.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some of the guests look oddly at the little boy standing before the man.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me, Mister.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man slowly turns and looks down at the boy standing next to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole is very shaky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches everything anxiously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole stares at Mr. Collins.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you Kyra's daddy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man's face begins to crumble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He nods, "yes" softly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole holds out the jewelry box.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It trembles with his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father just stares at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: It's for you...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: She wanted to tell you something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father becomes very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes fill with a storm of confusion and pain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After the longest time, the father reaches and gently takes the box out of Cole's small hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole begins to back away...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father gazes at Cole as he melts into the crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole reaches Malcolm and the two then slip out of the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father looks down in a daze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes to open the jewelry box.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His movements are slow and strained.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lifts the latch and open the box.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Collins stares at an unlabeled video cassette.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LIVING ROOM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People in the room start to turn as the T.V. comes on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Collins is seated now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE STATIC SNOW ON THE SCREEN IS QUICKLY REPLACED BY AN IMAGE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO PUPPETS DANCE ON STAGE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR KYRA'S VOICE SING FOR THE PUPPETS AS THEY DANCE AROUND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her father's face forms the most heartbreaking of smiles as he watches the performance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The entire room has stopped what they were doing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T.V. SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR FOOTSTEPS COMING UP THE STAIRS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The puppets go limp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The entire stage gets lifted up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see it carried away by Kyra.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We can view the whole bedroom now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera is seated on her desk in the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyra climbs in bed and pretends to be sleeping when the door opens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's Mrs. Collins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She carries in a tray of soup and a sandwich.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd watches in riveted silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father never takes his eyes off of the screen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image of the mother prepares the meal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She uncovers the fruit and the soup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Places a straw into the drink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then it happens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image of the mother walks to a closet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Opens it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An assortment of household cleaners and sponges are kept inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pulls out a bottle of floor cleaner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reads the label for the ingredients.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Walks back to the food tray, where she unscrews the cap on the floor cleaner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mother pours some into the cap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Checks it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: That's too much.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mother pours some into the bottle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The remainder goes into the child's soup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She replaces the cap and puts the bottle back in the closet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image of the mother turns to the bed carrying the tray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She places the food on a metallic rolling table and swings it over the bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Kyra, time for lunch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyra pretends to wake from a deep sleep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KYRA
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm feeling much better now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image of the mother smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINGS
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm glad, honey.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Time for your food.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KYRA
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Can I go outside, if I eat this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: We'll see.
{DIALOGUE}: You know how you get sick in the afternoon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyra picks up the spoon and takes a sip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her face crinkles at the taste.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up at her mother.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (video tape)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't say it tastes funny.
{DIALOGUE}: You know I don't like to hear that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyra slowly brings the spoon to her mouth and swallows another spoonful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The father SHUTS OFF THE TELEVISION with his trembling hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He presses his hands to his eyes like they're burning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ROOM IS UTTERLY SILENT.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DINING ROOM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Collins is seated at the dining room surrounded by friends and family.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She fixes one of the many bouquets of flowers on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It takes her a beat before she feels the stare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Standing in the doorway to the dining room is Mr. Collins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A group of ashen faced guests stand in the distance behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Husband and wife's eyes meet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Collins smiles softly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Collins' eyes tremble with tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: You were keeping her sick...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whole world stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mother's face registers confusion at first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then slow realization.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes glace at the many faces around her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks back at her husband.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His glare is painful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rage filling every cell of his body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears falling faster down his cheeks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Collins turns her attention back to the flowers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She concentrates with all her strength.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hands begin to shake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. COLLINS
{META_DATA}: (to no one)
{DIALOGUE}: I took care of her...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her words are met with ice cold stares.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The first tears stream down her face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pretty flowers of consolation in her hand tumble to the floor.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOUSE - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole sits on the swings next to Kyra's four-year-old sister.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She doesn't look up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm waits in the driveway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watches them from a distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole reaches into his pocket and pulls out the little FINGER PUPPET.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds it out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: You liked it, she said.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The four-year-old stares at the finger puppet, then quietly takes it in her small hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two children don't say anything for a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm glances to the house, where all movements in and out of the home has ceased.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole turns to the four-year-old.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She watched out for you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The little girl finally looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has the saddest eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOUR YEAR OLD
{DIALOGUE}: Kyra's not coming back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: Not anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The little girl stares down at the finger puppet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole lightly places a hand on her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing else is said.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing else is done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks across the two children on the swings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One mourning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One consoling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm takes it in, overwhelmed.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PROP ROOM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stanley Cunningham moves between two curtains and comes to a prop room door in the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts an ear to the door, listens and then knocks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a second, he enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Cunningham finds Cole sitting in a poor villager costume as a FEMALE TEACHER kneels next to him and makes final adjustments.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole and the woman glance at Mr. Cunningham.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. CUNNINGHAM
{DIALOGUE}: They're calling for the stable boy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Cunningham looks around the room and then directly at Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. CUNNINGHAM
{DIALOGUE}: Who were you talking to?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Female Teacher looks to Cole and nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FEMALE TEACHER
{DIALOGUE}: Poor Stanley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stands up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The entire left side of her face has been burnt horribly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grotesquely disfigured.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FEMALE TEACHER
{DIALOGUE}: My favorite student.
