{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The teacher hurries past Malcolm and down the hall without saying a word.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a yes?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The teacher scurries around a corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches her curiously.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. AUDITORIUM - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm moves quickly to a set of double doors and opens them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps into the DARKNESS OF THE AUDITORIUM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The play is in full swing... Cole and a large group of costumed children are on stage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole holds a broom and wears a worn-down costume.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands to the side -- hidden by others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A boy in a shiny-armored costume walks to the center of the stage where a large cardboard stone is seated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sparkling HANDLE sticks out of the top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The armored boy tries to lift it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It won't budge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bobby, the chubby boy from the party, is dressed in a magician's costume.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is Merlin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps forward.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Only he who is pure of heart can take the sword from the stone.
