{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks right at Cole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Let the boy try.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The group of villagers on the stage LAUGH AND MOCK THE SUGGESTION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tommy Tammisimo is dressed in a mismatched costume -- he hops around, clearly embarrassed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOMMY
{META_DATA}: (half-heartedly)
{DIALOGUE}: But he's the stable boy.
{DIALOGUE}: He cleans after the horses.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Silence village idiot!
{DIALOGUE}: Let the boy step forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tommy turns a deep shade of red and hobbles off the stage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merlin looks to Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles a true friend's smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Arthur...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole hesitates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not because he's acting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He really hesitates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It takes him a moment before he steps forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole steps up to the stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He places his hand around the handle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Begins to pull.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sword starts to come out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The villagers GASP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole raises the shiny sword out of the stone and high above his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merlin and everyone on stage bows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SILENCE FILLS THE AUDITORIUM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches his client, standing unafraid in the spot light for the first time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The villagers rise and rush to Cole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They scoop him up and carry him around the stage in celebration.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole chuckles and then starts laughing as the group of eight-year-olds try unsuccessfully to keep him up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They slowly sag and then collapse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All the students are laughing as they try to untangle themselves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches with utter joy as Cole becomes indistinguishable among of a group of twenty children giggling and enjoying themselves on stage.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SCHOOL LOBBY - LATE AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rain comes down a little stronger now on the stained glass window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm sits on the stairs in the lobby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole walks back and forth in front of him.
