{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When she speaks, her words are extremely controlled.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, that's very wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: Grandma's gone.
{DIALOGUE}: You know that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She wanted me to tell you--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: Cole, please stop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She wanted me to tell you, she saw you dance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's eyes lock on Cole's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She said when you were little, you and her had a fight right before your dance recital.
{DIALOGUE}: You thought she didn't come to see you dance.
{DIALOGUE}: She did.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn brings her hands to her mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She hid in the back so you wouldn't see... She said you were like an angel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn begins to cry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{DIALOGUE}: She said, you came to her where they buried her.
{DIALOGUE}: Asked her a question... She said the answer is "Everyday."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn covers her face with her hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tears roll out through her fingers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: What did you ask?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks at her son.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She barely gets the words out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (crying)
{DIALOGUE}: Do I make her proud?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cole moves closer to Lynn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She cradles him in her arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mother and son hold each other tight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE PULL BACK FROM THE WINDSHIELD, BACK PAST THE FRONT BUMPER WHERE THE FIGURE OF THE BLOODED WOMAN STANDS STARING AT COLE AND HIS MOTHER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE SEE A MANGLED BIKE PULLED OUT FROM THE REAR-ENDED CAR ON THE SIDEWALK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE MOVE UP AND AWAY FROM THE RAIN-SOAKED BRIDGE.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MALCOLM'S HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm walks quietly down the sidewalk towards his home.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LIVING ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm enters the living room and smiles at what he sees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna is asleep in a chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's curled up in a ball.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a way, she looks like a little girl.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their WEDDING VIDEO PLAYS SOFTLY ON THE TELEVISION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches himself and Anna cutting their wedding cake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE CROWD APPLAUDS AS THEY FEED EACH OTHER PIECES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm turns from the television and takes a seat next to Anna.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gazes upon his wife softly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Anna, I've been so lost.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I need my best friend.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm gazes for a beat before looking down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: I miss you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes move back up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at his sleeping wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANNA'S TALKING IN HER SLEEP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm can't believe it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I miss you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her lips move again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eyes never open.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Why, Malcolm?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: What, Anna?
{DIALOGUE}: What did I do?
{DIALOGUE}: What's made you so sad?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Why did you leave me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't leave you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She becomes silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna falls back into deep sleep, her arm slides down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOMETHING SHINY FALLS OUT AND ROLLS ON THE GROUND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes watch as it comes to a stop... Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gazes curiously at a GOLD WEDDING BAND laying on the wood floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Confusion washes over his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks to Anna's hand... An identical gold wedding ring sits on her finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks down at his own hand... HIS WEDDING RING IS GONE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm is completely lost.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes a couple steps back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks around in confusion...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes come to rest on the door to his basement office.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks in disbelief at the set of DEAD BOLT LOCKS on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm doesn't know what the hell's going on... His eyes are drawn to the dining table... Only ONE PLACE SETTING is out on the tabletop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes search again -- they finally lock on the WEDDING VIDEO PLAYING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm watches images of himself on the screen... His eyes fill with a storm of emotions...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks to Anna's face and becomes very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON ANNA... TILL HER SLEEPING FACE FILLS THE FRAME... IT'S NOW WE NOTICE FOR THE FIRST TIME, THAT ANNA'S BREATHS ARE FORMING TINY CLOUDS IN THE COLD AIR.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (like he's falling down a deep hole)
{DIALOGUE}: No...
{META_DATA}: SLAM CUT:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: FLASHBACK: INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VIOLENT GUN SHOTS RING THROUGH THE BEDROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna rushes across the room to a crumpled Malcolm laying on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's hands are clutched at his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna pries his hands away to reveal the tiniest tear in his shirt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna's eyes catch something dark -- moving... A POOL OF BLOOD IS FORMING UNDER MALCOLM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slowly turns him over on his side... A horrific sight... An enormous exit wound on his lower back pours out blood uncontrollably.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's jaw is locked open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His breaths are long and strained.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANNA IS SCREAMING, BUT HER VOICE SOUNDS FAR AWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's open jaw releases a long strained breath and then becomes silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna tries to cover the wound with her hands desperately.
{META_DATA}: SLAM CUT:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: PRESENT: INT. LIVING ROOM - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (screaming)
{DIALOGUE}: ANNA!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MALCOLM'S VOICE SHAKES THE ROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna just sleeps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm staggers back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His breathing erratic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes a seat across from her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at his wife and suddenly becomes very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna's still curled up asleep, but tears are falling from her shut eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Don't cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna doesn't move, but her tears seem to fall a little faster.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: I think I have to go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's mind is racing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (realizing)
{DIALOGUE}: I just needed to do a couple of things.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: And I needed to tell you something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: You were never second... Ever.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm gazes at his wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears fall from both their eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: You sleep now, Anna.
{DIALOGUE}: Everything will be different in the morning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna lays still.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: Goodnight, Malcolm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Goodnight, sweetheart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room falls into silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm sits still across from his wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drinks her in with his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm leans back in the chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly closes his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They close shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE ARE TIGHT ON ANNA... WE SEE HER SOFT BREATHS FORMING A TINY CLOUD IN THE COLD AIR...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WITH EACH BREATH, THEY BECOME LESS AND LESS VISIBLE... THE ROOM BECOMING LESS AND LESS COLD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOON HER BREATHS AREN'T VISIBLE AT ALL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SHE BREATHES GENTLY, FALLING BACK INTO A PEACEFUL SLEEP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE PULL BACK to reveal Anna alone in the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE WEDDING VIDEO PLAYS ITS LAST SCENES... MALCOLM IS AT THE MICROPHONE ON THE DANCE FLOOR IN FRONT OF ALL THE GUESTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HE'S HOLDING A GLASS OF WINE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: ...I think I've had too much to drink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm smiles as he takes a sip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guests chuckle as they watch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: I just have to say, this day today has been one very special day... I wish we all could stay and play.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd erupts in LAUGHTER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (on tape)
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm looks around at everyone's smiling faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm takes his time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks just past the camera.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{DIALOGUE}: Anna, I never thought I'd feel the things I'm feeling.
{DIALOGUE}: I never thought I'd be able to stand up in front of my friends and family and tell them what's inside me... Today I can...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Malcolm's eyes fill with water.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MALCOLM
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: Anna Crowe... I am in love.
{DIALOGUE}: In love I am.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK:
{META_DATA}: THE END
